{"parse":{"title":"Open management education","pageid":34652058,"revid":581404646,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Open management education</b> refers to business and management programs and courses making use of <a href=\"/wiki/Open_educational_resources\" title=\"Open educational resources\">open educational resources</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Open_content\" title=\"Open content\">open content</a>. The main idea is to develop competences by re-use, combination and adaption of freely accessible, existing resources.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Goals_and_purpose\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Goals and purpose</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Challenges\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Challenges</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Access_to_open_management_education\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Access to open management education</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Goals_and_purpose\">Goals and purpose</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Open_management_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Goals and purpose\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Programs and trainings in business and management are often not affordable, especially for SMEs or for people in less developed countries. Therefore, open management education seems like a promising alternative for many stakeholders.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Challenges\">Challenges</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Open_management_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Challenges\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It is still an ongoing discussion which <a href=\"/wiki/Business_models\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Business models\">business models</a> could be applied, such as sharing or add-on models. However, the domain is still developing and no business model has become mainstream. A good discussion can be found by Downes (2007).<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Another challenge is to find simple tools to adapt (the sometimes complex) resources.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Access_to_open_management_education\">Access to open management education</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Open_management_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Access to open management education\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>There are many repositories, databases and web access points, some of them listed here:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://learn.openscout.net\">OpenScout</a> providing access to global resources in the business and management sector.  It is possible to search for competences to be achieved and to get help with tools for adaptation (e.g. internationalizing materials, adapting the design, contextualizing), see also the Wikipedia entry for <a href=\"/wiki/Openscout\" title=\"Openscout\">Openscout</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.khanacademy.org\">The Khan Academy</a> provides a variety of business courses.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/MIT_OpenCourseWare\" title=\"MIT OpenCourseWare\">MIT OpenCourseWare</a> access to courses from MIT, some of them related to management</li>\n<li>MERLOT <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.merlot.org/merlot/materials.htm?category=2202\">Repository</a> (Category Business)</li>\n<li>Globe Info (Federation of Repositories): (no browsing, just use keywords such as management or better more specific) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.globe-info.org/\">Search page</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Open_management_education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Kalz, M., Specht, M., Nadolski, R., Bastiaens, Y., Leirs, N., and Pawlowski, J.M. (2010) OpenScout: Competence based management education with community-improved open educational resources, 17th EDINEBConference: Crossing borders in Education and Work-based Learning, London, UK, June 2010, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/1820/2452\">[1]</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Downes, S. (2007): Models for Sustainable Open Educational Resources in Interdisciplinary Journal of Knowledge and Learning Objects 3 29-44 February 27, 2007. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.downes.ca/post/33401\">[2]</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Mikroyannidis, Alexander; Okada, Alexandra and Connolly, Teresa (2011). Sharing practices and experiences on the authoring and adaptation of Open Educational Resources. In: Open Educational Resources 2011, 11\u201313 May 2011, Manchester, UK. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://oro.open.ac.uk/29265/\">[3]</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2207\nCached time: 20180922011553\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.032 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.042 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 111/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 359/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 89/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1690/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.003/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 525 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   23.091      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   23.091      1 -total\n  9.71%    2.242      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:34652058-0!canonical and timestamp 20180922011553 and revision id 581404646\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Management_education"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Business models"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"MIT OpenCourseWare"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Open content"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Open educational resources"}